        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 5:27PM CDT by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Grand Saline, or 10 miles northeast of Canton. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Grand Saline around 535 PM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Oakland, Jones, and
Pruitt.

This includes Interstate 20 between mile markers 534 and 535.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
